ormal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">skin rash, itching, burning, redness, dryness,</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">thinning or softening of your skin,</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">skin rash or irritation around your mouth,</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">swollen hair follicles,</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">spider veins,</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">numbness or tingling,</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">changes in color of treated skin,</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">blisters,</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">pimples,</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">crusting of treated skin, or</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">stretch marks.</li></ul><h5 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; clear: both; margin: 0px 0px 2rem; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-weight: var(--rio-heading-font-weight,600); font-size: calc(1.8rem * var(--rio-typo-ratio,1)); line-height: var(--rio-heading-line-height,var(--rio-body-line-height)); letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; color: var(--rio-heading-color,var(--rio-body-color)); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Use and Administration</h5><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Apply a thin film of Elocon Pomet Cream to the affected skin areas once daily. Elocon Pomet Cream may be used in pediatric patients 2 years of age or older. Since safety and efficacy of Elocon Pomet Cream have not been established in pediatric patients below 2 years of age</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Therapy should be discontinued when control is achieved. If no improvement is seen within 2 weeks, reassessment of diagnosis may be necessary. Safety and efficacy of Elocon Pomet Cream in pediatric patients for more than 3 weeks of use have not been established.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Elocon Pomet Cream should not be used with occlusive dressings unless directed by a physician. Elocon Pomet Cream should not be applied in the diaper area if the child still requires diapers or plastic pants, as these garments may constitute occlusive dressing.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Elocon Pomet Cream is for topical use only. It is not for oral, ophthalmic, or intravaginal use.</p><h5 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; clear: both; margin: 0px 0px 2rem; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-weight: var(--rio-heading-font-weight,600); font-size: calc(1.8rem * var(--rio-typo-ratio,1)); line-height: var(--rio-heading-line-height,var(--rio-body-line-height)); letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; color: var(--rio-heading-color,var(--rio-body-color)); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Side effect of Elocon Pomet</h5><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Because clinical trials are conducted under widely varying conditions, adverse reaction rates observed in the clinical trials of a drug cannot be directly compared to rates in the clinical trials of another drug and may not reflect the rates observed in clinical practice.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">In controlled clinical trials involving 319 subjects, the incidence of adverse reactions associated with the use of Elocon 0.1% Cream was 1.6%. Reported reactions included burning, pruritus, and skin atrophy. Reports of rosacea associated with the use of Elocon 0.1% Cream have also been received. In controlled clinical trials (n=74) involving pediatric subjects 2 to 12 years of age, the incidence of adverse experiences associated with the use of Elocon 0.1% Cream was approximately 7%. Reported reactions included stinging, pruritus, and furunculosis.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">The following adverse reactions were reported to be possibly or probably related to treatment with Elocon 0.1% Cream during clinical trials in 4% of 182 pediatric subjects 6 months to 2 years of age: decreased glucocorticoid levels, 2; paresthesia, 2; folliculitis, 1; moniliasis, 1; bacterial infection, 1; skin depigmentation, 1. The following signs of skin atrophy were also observed among 97 subjects treated with Elocon 0.1% Cream in a clinical trial: shininess, 4; telangiectasia, 1; loss of elasticity, 4; loss of normal skin markings, 4; thinness, 1; and bruising, 1.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">The following additional local adverse reactions have been reported with topical corticosteroids, but may occur more frequently with the use of occlusive dressings. These reactions are: irritation, dryness, folliculitis, hypertrichosis, acneiform eruptions, hypopigmentation, perioral dermatitis, allergic contact dermatitis, secondary infection, striae, and miliaria.</p>', NULL, 1150.00, NULL, '[]', '[]', '[]', 1, 1, 1, 0, NULL, 10.00, 'percent', NULL, 'amount', 'flat_rate', NULL, 0, 'Elocon Pomet', NULL, 'uploads/products/meta/FYtND9hQVjQpRdUtO1hivOtuTf6cAeE85baXb4pc.jpg', NULL, 'Elocon-Pomet-Metrhem-01-30gm-RoKC8', '2022-03-20 07:13:57', '2022-03-22 17:06:46'),
(56, 'Xeragel Silicone Ointment 10gm', 'admin', 394, 25, 99, 318, 0, '[\"uploads\\/products\\/photos\\/ZAXtVfQdHChDhH47aQ9U1WGwxuMM6vG98JGql9sj.jpg\"]', 'uploads/products/thumbnail/Y3r3oUEASWgbWn7KB5hmbgrVaCkOZBq7ZeeMi2dw.jpg', 'uploads/products/featured/m4XNw5qDlKIuOsW1tSV7OyGhis3vdjt4XC1zLawq.jpg', 'uploads/products/flash_deal/KXCjAtsFWPtEPVdZYUpCTFRtUqig7pbdXU39c8US.jpg', 'youtube', NULL, '', '20220304', '<h2>Xeragel Silicone Ointment 10gm<br></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.5rem; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">is a silica gel 0% transparent indicated for the treatment of hypertrophic scars and Keloids, post-surgery scars and other types of scars caused by injury or burn. Highly effective for use on facial scars that are exposed, both new and old. It is a clear gel that reduces the size, thickness, height and color of all types of scars. Due to its high viscosity, it is ideal for the treatment of scars by episiotomies, where the gel is fixed and allows to treat the scar in the area with a high efficiency.</p><h5 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; clear: both; margin: 0px 0px 2rem; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-weight: var(--rio-heading-font-weight,600); font-size: calc(1.8rem * var(--rio-typo-ratio,1)); line-height: var(--rio-heading-line-height,var(--rio-body-line-height)); letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none; color: var(--rio-heading-color,var(--rio-body-color)); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">How to use</h5><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding-inline-start: 20px; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Clean and dry the scar before each application.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Xeragel Silicone Ointment apply a generous amount of Xeragel about all the scar.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Repeat several times a day for 8 weeks or until scar stops responding to treatment.</li></ul>', NULL, 1690.00, NULL, '[]', '[]', '[]', 1, 1, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, 'amount', NULL, 'amount', 'flat_rate', NULL, 0, 'Xeragel Silicone Ointment', 'Xeragel Silicone Ointment', NULL, NULL, 'Xeragel-Silicone-Ointment-10gm-KpUpU', '2022-03-20 07:27:16', '2022-03-22 17:07:15');
